inlineContent.text: Use color to customize your app’s appearance, communicate status, and help people visualize data. To learn more about using color in your apps, see
provides a list of class properties that create adaptable and fixed colors such as blue, green, purple, and more.

also offers properties to specify system-provided colors for UI elements such as labels, text, and buttons. You can create color objects by specifying color component values such as RGB, hue, and saturation. You can also create colors from other color objects and even create a pattern-based color from an image.
Most developers have no need to subclass

. The only time subclassing might be necessary is if you require support for additional color spaces or color models. If you do subclass, the properties and methods you add must be safe to use from multiple threads.
